[src:bqn-array/point-free-programming] jq is a JSON-oriented programming language in which the `|` symbol is used to connect filters to form a pipeline in a familiar way.
[src:bqn-array/point-free-programming] Although similar to Unix pipelines, jq pipelines allow the incoming data to be sent to more than one recipient on the RHS of the `|` as though in parallel.
